(Test format string interpolation - comprehensive tests)

(Basic variable interpolation)
a text called "name" is "Alice".
a number called "age" is 25.
Print "Hello, {name}!".
Print "Age: {age}".

(Number base formatting)
a number called "val" is 255.
Print "Decimal: {val}".
Print "Hex lower: {val:x}".
Print "Hex upper: {val:X}".
Print "Binary: {val:b}".
Print "Octal: {val:o}".

(Float precision)
a float called "pi" is 3.14159.
Print "Pi default: {pi}".
Print "Pi .2: {pi:.2}".
Print "Pi .0: {pi:.0}".

(Integer padding)
a number called "small" is 42.
Print "Padded: [{small:6}]".
Print "Zero-pad: [{small:06}]".

(Escaped braces with variable)
Print "Value is {{val}} = {val}".
